1
00:01:55,099 --> 00:01:56,060
Mr. Fan

2
00:01:57,140 --> 00:01:59,060
I heard you're a retired professor

3
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:00,500
with very high academic standing

4
00:02:00,659 --> 00:02:03,260
so I have a few questions to ask you

5
00:02:03,379 --> 00:02:04,579
You've heard about that?

6
00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:06,480
Bring it here, let me see

7
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,260
Here, this one

8
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:08,280
You're Yingzi, right?

9
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:09,960
Hello

10
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,639
You can ask me questions too, you know

11
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,439
You don't have to ask him

12
00:02:13,639 --> 00:02:14,560
Ask you?

13
00:02:14,719 --> 00:02:16,039
Are you up to it?

14
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,479
Yeah, President Li

15
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:19,180
This is in English

16
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,560
Do you understand it?

17
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,479
I don't understand?

18
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:22,759
Yeah right

19
00:02:23,759 --> 00:02:25,439
When I went to India for business back then

20
00:02:25,919 --> 00:02:27,919
even the beggars there understood English

21
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:29,479
President Li

22
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,180
Then tell us

23
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:31,120
what this means

24
00:02:34,599 --> 00:02:36,039
The meaning of this paragraph is...

25
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:38,120
Why should I tell you?

26
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,319
Didn't you say you understood?

27
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,840
Do I have to tell you just because I understand?

28
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:43,879
Is that so?

29
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,500
If you can translate

30
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:46,439
this sentence

31
00:02:47,479 --> 00:02:49,000
I'll give you one hundred yuan

32
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,860
Deal?

33
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:50,659
Deal

34
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,719
The meaning of this passage is

35
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,400
Heaven gave me talent for a reason

36
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:58,800
And a mouse's son can dig a hole

37
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,599
I earned this hundred bucks easily

38
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:01,919
Come back, come back

39
00:03:01,919 --> 00:03:02,539
Put it down

40
00:03:02,879 --> 00:03:04,060
I earned this hundred bucks

41
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,400
You translated it wrong

42
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,219
Why are you taking it?

43
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,259
You just said

44
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:09,099
you'd pay a hundred if I translated it

45
00:03:09,099 --> 00:03:10,840
You didn't say I had to translate it correctly

46
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:11,960
Bye-bye now

47
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:12,960
You're cheating

48
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:13,680
Give it to me

49
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:14,539
Give me the money

50
00:03:30,879 --> 00:03:31,560
Xiaolan

51
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,879
Where have you been?

52
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:33,719
I went shopping

53
00:03:33,719 --> 00:03:35,479
Zhongguancun No. 1 was really lively

54
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:38,120
How can you go shopping during work hours?

55
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:41,919
What are you doing?

56
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:44,319
Did you give Gou'er Ye his medicine today?

57
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,800
I actually forgot about that

58
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,199
How could you forget that?

59
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,080
If Dr. Chang finds out

60
00:03:50,199 --> 00:03:51,400
How could he possibly know?

61
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,319
If he finds out

62
00:03:53,319 --> 00:03:54,680
it means you snitched

63
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,280
Me?

64
00:03:58,719 --> 00:04:00,680
Gou'er Ye, time for your medicine.

65
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,280
Okay.

66
00:04:02,599 --> 00:04:03,400
Here.

67
00:04:03,599 --> 00:04:04,520
You take it.

68
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,520
What?

69
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,740
It's not for me.

70
00:04:06,740 --> 00:04:07,879
It's for you.

71
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:10,319
Don't be polite, I'm not hungry.

72
00:04:10,319 --> 00:04:11,360
You have to take it.

73
00:04:13,539 --> 00:04:14,099
What for?

74
00:04:14,439 --> 00:04:15,139
This isn't medicine.

75
00:04:15,139 --> 00:04:16,040
It's chocolate.

76
00:04:16,439 --> 00:04:18,319
I won't take medicine if you don't give me chocolate.

77
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:20,279
For an old man your age,

78
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:21,339
why are you so greedy?

79
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:23,420
Fine, here you go.

80
00:04:23,519 --> 00:04:24,120
Here.

81
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:25,480
Xiaolan.

82
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,839
How can you give him chocolate?

83
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:29,000
This is my chocolate.

84
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,839
Gou'er Ye.

85
00:04:29,839 --> 00:04:31,040
You have diabetes.

86
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,160
You can't eat sweets.

87
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,680
You must never give him sweets again.

88
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,000
Or it could be dangerous.

89
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:36,959
Then what should I do?

90
00:04:36,959 --> 00:04:37,600
Without chocolate,

91
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,879
this old man won't take his medicine.

92
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,879
Figure something out.

93
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,319
Gou'er Ye.

94
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,360
Take your medicine first.

95
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:47,839
After the medicine, I'll buy you eight-treasure porridge.

96
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,720
Sugar-free.

97
00:04:48,879 --> 00:04:49,680
Is it sweet?

98
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:50,720
It's sweet.

99
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:52,360
Come on, take the medicine first.

100
00:04:54,319 --> 00:04:55,439
This medicine...

101
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:59,160
Xiaolan, did you get the wrong medicine?

102
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:00,259
Impossible.

103
00:05:00,259 --> 00:05:00,959
How could I...

104
00:05:01,959 --> 00:05:02,959
You really got it wrong.

105
00:05:03,319 --> 00:05:05,079
Look, this is so dangerous.

106
00:05:05,079 --> 00:05:06,360
Go change it immediately.

107
00:05:06,399 --> 00:05:07,199
Okay.

108
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:11,920
You have to take this medicine away too.

109
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,240
It can't stay here.

110
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,360
Stand there.

111
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,160
Director Chang.

112
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,639
Has Gou'er Ye taken his medicine?

113
00:05:17,839 --> 00:05:18,639
He has.

114
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,120
You get some rest.

115
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,360
Xiaofang.

116
00:05:24,279 --> 00:05:25,639
It's not that I don't let you eat snacks.

117
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:26,959
But it's working hours right now.

118
00:05:27,319 --> 00:05:28,120
It wasn't me.

119
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,040
This chocolate is...

120
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:31,019
That chocolate is for me to eat.

121
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,040
How could you give Gou'er Ye chocolate?

122
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,199
Do you know what condition he has?

123
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,420
I know.

124
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:40,319
He has diabetes.

125
00:05:40,319 --> 00:05:41,480
You knew, yet you still gave it to him?

126
00:05:41,899 --> 00:05:43,399
If he develops ketones, who's responsible?

127
00:05:43,819 --> 00:05:45,420
I didn't give him chocolate.

128
00:05:45,459 --> 00:05:46,819
I was trying to give him his medicine.

129
00:05:47,220 --> 00:05:47,980
Just to give him medicine,

130
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:49,100
you let him eat chocolate?

131
00:05:49,699 --> 00:05:50,540
What medicine is this?

132
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:54,519
Do you know you took the wrong medicine?

133
00:05:54,939 --> 00:05:56,060
This is the wrong one.

134
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:57,560
This isn't for Gou'er Ye.

135
00:05:57,740 --> 00:05:59,379
Xiaofang, you have disappointed me so much.

136
00:05:59,379 --> 00:06:00,860
Do you know that giving a patient the wrong medicine

137
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:01,800
can be extremely dangerous?

138
00:06:02,339 --> 00:06:03,279
You and Xiaolan, the two of you,

139
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:04,220
are both currently on probation.

140
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:06,120
Only one of you can stay at the center.

141
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:07,540
I originally intended to keep you.

142
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:08,600
I really didn't expect you...

143
00:06:09,139 --> 00:06:09,939
Dr. Chang.

144
00:06:09,939 --> 00:06:10,939
This isn't the one. Xiaofang...

145
00:06:10,939 --> 00:06:11,899
took the wrong one.

146
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:13,579
It should be this bottle.

147
00:06:14,259 --> 00:06:15,060
I...

148
00:06:15,379 --> 00:06:16,019
Look at this.

149
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:18,019
You two came from the same place.

150
00:06:18,019 --> 00:06:19,420
How can your professional skills differ so much?

151
00:06:19,699 --> 00:06:21,500
Can't you learn more from Xiaolan?

152
00:06:21,660 --> 00:06:22,980
Director Chang, this was actually...

153
00:06:22,980 --> 00:06:25,300
Actually, I was supposed to feed Gou'er Ye.

154
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:27,019
But I heard Grandma Jin coughing just now,

155
00:06:27,019 --> 00:06:28,459
so I went to check on her for Xiaofang.

156
00:06:28,459 --> 00:06:30,079
I didn't expect that in just this moment...

157
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,420
Director Chang, please don't criticize her anymore.

158
00:06:32,420 --> 00:06:33,860
She was just trying to help me out.

159
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,860
She can't even do her own job properly,

160
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:36,819
yet she tries to help others?

161
00:06:36,819 --> 00:06:38,300
No, she meant well.

162
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:39,480
Please don't criticize her.

163
00:06:39,819 --> 00:06:41,720
Xiaofang, go check on Grandma Jin.

164
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:43,800
Come back.

165
00:06:43,939 --> 00:06:44,420
Come back.

166
00:06:45,579 --> 00:06:47,199
Dr. Chang, are there any other instructions?

167
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:50,100
Your shift leader,

168
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:51,100
Sister Niu,

169
00:06:51,259 --> 00:06:52,420
has taken two weeks of sick leave.

170
00:06:53,339 --> 00:06:54,420
So during this period,

171
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:55,740
the acting shift leader...

172
00:06:57,980 --> 00:06:58,860
Xiaolan, you do it.

173
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,620
Thank you, Dr. Chang.

174
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:02,339
I, Xiaolan, promise to complete the task.

175
00:07:03,139 --> 00:07:03,939
Gou'er Ye.

176
00:07:03,939 --> 00:07:04,620
I'm leaving now.

177
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,339
Remember to take your medicine.

178
00:07:05,339 --> 00:07:06,220
Take your medicine.

179
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,720
Xiaofang

180
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:21,279
Go check if today's delivery is here.

181
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,360
But I'm giving Grandma Jin her medicine.

182
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,439
I can't step away.

183
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,759
You dare disobey the boss?

184
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:28,800
If I leave,

185
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,079
who will watch Grandma Jin?

186
00:07:30,079 --> 00:07:30,839
It's fine.

187
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,160
I'm here.

188
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,639
Then you have to be careful.

189
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:37,439
Don't let her choke.

190
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:40,079
I know, she won't.

191
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:41,519
Grandma Jin,

192
00:07:41,519 --> 00:07:43,019
let me give you your medicine.

193
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,279
You want to sleep here?

194
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,060
Here.

195
00:07:53,519 --> 00:07:54,240
What's wrong?

196
00:07:56,660 --> 00:07:57,899
Why are you coughing?

197
00:07:58,579 --> 00:07:59,620
A monk?

198
00:08:00,379 --> 00:08:02,139
From which temple?

199
00:08:02,939 --> 00:08:04,259
Talk about a tangent.

200
00:08:04,259 --> 00:08:05,060
Hey.

201
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:06,819
What is going on here?

202
00:08:06,899 --> 00:08:08,139
Royal Physician Sun, it's my fault.

203
00:08:08,139 --> 00:08:09,420
I forgot to remind Xiaofang today

204
00:08:09,420 --> 00:08:10,860
to suction Grandma Jin's phlegm.

205
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,100
What?

206
00:08:13,980 --> 00:08:15,480
You got the munchies?

207
00:08:16,459 --> 00:08:18,819
Who doesn't love a tasty treat?

208
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,500
It's such a routine procedure.

209
00:08:21,019 --> 00:08:21,899
Does it need reminding?

210
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:24,939
Isn't she on probation?

211
00:08:24,939 --> 00:08:25,620
She lacks experience.

212
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:26,939
It's understandable.

213
00:08:26,939 --> 00:08:28,740
I'll suction Grandma Jin right now.

214
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:29,699
About this...

215
00:08:29,699 --> 00:08:31,839
please don't tell Director Chang.

216
00:08:32,659 --> 00:08:33,580
That won't do.

217
00:08:33,659 --> 00:08:34,460
This matter...

218
00:08:34,539 --> 00:08:37,139
I must report to Director Chang immediately.

219
00:08:37,460 --> 00:08:39,019
What? Sleeping?

220
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:42,460
Didn't I just wake up from my nap?

221
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:44,940
Don't! I'll suction the phlegm right now.

222
00:08:45,659 --> 00:08:46,700
No need.

223
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:47,440
Well...

224
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,620
This morning,

225
00:08:49,059 --> 00:08:50,559
Xiaofang already did it for me.

226
00:08:51,340 --> 00:08:53,059
You can hear again all of a sudden?

227
00:08:58,460 --> 00:08:59,259
Xiaolan.

228
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,179
Grandma Jin, have an orange.

229
00:09:01,899 --> 00:09:02,779
Why is it that

230
00:09:02,899 --> 00:09:04,600
you're the one looking after Grandma Jin now?

231
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:06,139
Xiaofang said

232
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,080
she had to go out for something.

233
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:09,340
Here.

234
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:09,820
Hmph.

235
00:09:10,139 --> 00:09:10,980
Just as I thought.

236
00:09:25,419 --> 00:09:26,460
How is this couplet?

237
00:09:27,139 --> 00:09:27,940
Is it neat?

238
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:31,539
Not bad, not bad at all.

239
00:09:32,259 --> 00:09:33,860
Noun matches noun.

240
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:35,500
Verb matches verb.

241
00:09:35,860 --> 00:09:37,259
Adjective matches adjective.

242
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:38,919
Typo matches typo.

243
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,559
Hey!

244
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,779
Why can't you say anything nice?

245
00:09:42,220 --> 00:09:43,259
Hello, grandpas.

246
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:45,139
Xiaofang is here.

247
00:09:45,379 --> 00:09:46,220
Is there a problem?

248
00:09:46,379 --> 00:09:47,539
Do you need my advice?

249
00:09:47,539 --> 00:09:48,299
No.

250
00:09:48,340 --> 00:09:49,700
It's just that I'm off duty today.

251
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:50,980
I want to go into town for a walk.

252
00:09:51,019 --> 00:09:52,899
Is there anything you two need to buy?

253
00:09:52,899 --> 00:09:54,340
I can bring it back for you.

254
00:09:54,659 --> 00:09:55,860
Then first help me...

255
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:57,320
...get an ink cartridge.

256
00:09:57,419 --> 00:09:57,899
Okay.

257
00:09:57,899 --> 00:09:59,379
Buy me a bottle of Zhonghua ink.

258
00:09:59,379 --> 00:09:59,820
Sure.

259
00:10:00,019 --> 00:10:00,480
By the way.

260
00:10:00,659 --> 00:10:02,899
If you pass by a pharmacy...

261
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:05,299
...buy me a pair of those magnetic insoles.

262
00:10:05,539 --> 00:10:06,700
The kind that cures foot odor.

263
00:10:07,139 --> 00:10:07,879
You have foot odor?

264
00:10:08,419 --> 00:10:10,460
I hadn't noticed until you mentioned it.

265
00:10:11,059 --> 00:10:12,019
Who has foot odor?

266
00:10:12,019 --> 00:10:13,059
I'm buying them for you.

267
00:10:13,059 --> 00:10:14,899
When you take off your shoes, the smell makes me dizzy.

268
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:15,899
My feet smell?

269
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:17,419
Slander!

270
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:18,899
Xiaofang.

271
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:20,940
Buy me a magnetic herbal pillow.

272
00:10:21,539 --> 00:10:23,220
The kind that treats snoring.

273
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:25,740
You snore when you sleep?

274
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:26,580
I don't snore.

275
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:27,399
He snores.

276
00:10:27,559 --> 00:10:29,159
His snoring is outrageous.

277
00:10:29,659 --> 00:10:31,340
Keeps me up all night.

278
00:10:31,659 --> 00:10:32,460
Who snores?

279
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:33,539
You are spreading rumors.

280
00:10:33,539 --> 00:10:34,860
If you don't believe me, let's listen tonight.

281
00:10:35,299 --> 00:10:36,299
Then who has smelly feet?

282
00:10:36,299 --> 00:10:37,340
Smell them right now.

283
00:10:37,460 --> 00:10:38,980
Knock it off, don't embarrass yourself.

284
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:40,379
Grandpas, please stop arguing.

285
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:41,740
The things you want to buy...

286
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:42,700
...I've written them down.

287
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:43,980
I'll go buy them for you now.

288
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:44,700
Don't go yet.

289
00:10:45,139 --> 00:10:46,220
We have to give you the money.

290
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:48,059
No need, we can settle it when I get back.

291
00:10:48,059 --> 00:10:48,980
I use WeChat Pay.

292
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:49,779
It's very convenient.

293
00:10:49,779 --> 00:10:50,759
Take it first.

294
00:10:51,019 --> 00:10:51,860
After you buy them...

295
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:52,860
...we'll settle the difference.

296
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:54,580
Right. What if mine isn't enough?

297
00:10:54,580 --> 00:10:55,940
Use Professor Fan's money to cover it.

298
00:10:55,940 --> 00:10:56,340
Don't.

299
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:57,820
If his money isn't enough, don't buy it for him.

300
00:10:57,820 --> 00:10:58,659
Here, take it.

301
00:10:58,659 --> 00:10:59,740
Really, no need, Grandpa.

302
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:00,100
Take it.

303
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:00,659
When I get back...

304
00:11:00,799 --> 00:11:01,700
How can we not give you money?

305
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:02,419
Aha!

306
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,340
I've caught you this time, haven't I?

307
00:11:04,379 --> 00:11:06,019
Xiaofang, you have some nerve.

308
00:11:06,019 --> 00:11:07,700
Daring to solicit red envelopes privately.

309
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:10,759
Who solicited red envelopes?

310
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:11,559
I can testify.

311
00:11:11,779 --> 00:11:12,460
She didn't ask for it.

312
00:11:13,299 --> 00:11:14,179
This red envelope is...

313
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:15,539
What red envelope?

314
00:11:15,779 --> 00:11:18,059
This money is for her to buy things for us.

315
00:11:18,059 --> 00:11:19,580
Giving things isn't allowed either.

316
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,879
Who gave things?

317
00:11:21,019 --> 00:11:22,860
This money is for her...

318
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:24,580
...to buy things on our behalf.

319
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:25,179
That's right.

320
00:11:25,179 --> 00:11:26,059
Grandpas.

321
00:11:26,059 --> 00:11:27,340
What are you afraid of?

322
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:29,019
If there's a problem, file a complaint.

323
00:11:29,019 --> 00:11:29,860
Don't worry.

324
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:31,580
She doesn't dare do anything to you.

325
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:33,299
Xiaolan, you...

326
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:34,820
...you are bullying people too much.

327
00:11:34,820 --> 00:11:35,340
That's right.

328
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:37,019
Don't falsely accuse good people.

329
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:39,059
Let's go.

330
00:11:39,059 --> 00:11:40,779
Come with me to reason with Director Chang.

331
00:11:40,779 --> 00:11:42,139
Who are you scaring with the Director?

332
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:43,299
You think I...

333
00:11:44,259 --> 00:11:45,460
...wouldn't dare?

334
00:11:46,299 --> 00:11:48,379
Thinking just because someone protects you, you're fine.

335
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:49,980
Your probation is almost up.

336
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:51,340
Watch yourself.

337
00:11:54,299 --> 00:11:56,139
I think you're the one who needs to be careful.

338
00:11:56,899 --> 00:11:58,139
You have too many wicked schemes.

339
00:11:58,139 --> 00:11:59,139
Watch out for premature beats.

340
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:00,840
I'm so pissed off.

341
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,879
Hello, Dr. Chang.

342
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,360
This is Xiaolan.

343
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,240
I need to report a situation.

344
00:12:11,039 --> 00:12:14,200
My heart has been feeling really uncomfortable lately.

345
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,759
I might be having premature beats.

346
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:18,759
Who told you to be so scheming?

347
00:12:19,139 --> 00:12:19,799
You... I...

348
00:12:19,799 --> 00:12:20,779
Calm down.

349
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,159
Calm and objective.

350
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:23,919
Let's not get involved.

351
00:12:23,919 --> 00:12:24,679
We'll just investigate.

352
00:12:24,679 --> 00:12:26,720
No, she is just too infuriating.

353
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,779
Who do you think you are?

354
00:12:27,779 --> 00:12:28,600
That's enough.

355
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,419
Xiaofang, why are you being so polite with me?

356
00:12:37,419 --> 00:12:38,460
If I say take it, just take it.

357
00:12:38,460 --> 00:12:39,500
I really can't.

358
00:12:39,659 --> 00:12:40,820
The community has rules.

359
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:42,419
We can't accept gifts from patients.

360
00:12:42,659 --> 00:12:44,019
You're not accepting it.

361
00:12:44,179 --> 00:12:45,200
I'm giving it to you.

362
00:12:46,059 --> 00:12:47,620
Besides, I'm not a patient.

363
00:12:48,059 --> 00:12:49,100
That's still not allowed.

364
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:51,500
I say it's allowed, so it is.

365
00:12:51,659 --> 00:12:53,799
My daughter brought this back from a business trip.

366
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,799
One box for you.

367
00:12:55,059 --> 00:12:56,059
One box for Grandma Jin.

368
00:12:56,379 --> 00:12:57,299
Little Li.

369
00:12:57,820 --> 00:12:59,259
Is this for me?

370
00:12:59,259 --> 00:12:59,820
Yes.

371
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:01,139
It sticks to my teeth.

372
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:03,220
Just give it to Xiaofang.

373
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:03,700
You see?

374
00:13:04,220 --> 00:13:05,299
Grandma Jin has spoken.

375
00:13:05,299 --> 00:13:06,039
Just accept it.

376
00:13:06,179 --> 00:13:06,820
Try a piece first.

377
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,139
It's really delicious, I'm telling you.

378
00:13:08,139 --> 00:13:08,980
Really, try it.

379
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:10,759
Xiaogan sesame candy.

380
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:12,100
It's my favorite.

381
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:12,620
Really?

382
00:13:13,179 --> 00:13:14,100
You like it too?

383
00:13:14,340 --> 00:13:15,340
That's great.

384
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:16,419
Then these two boxes...

385
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:17,659
I'm giving them to Xiaofang.

386
00:13:18,779 --> 00:13:19,460
President Li...

387
00:13:19,460 --> 00:13:20,779
I... I...

388
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:22,379
Grandma Jin.

389
00:13:24,659 --> 00:13:25,460
Royal Physician Sun.

390
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:26,139
Come take a look, quick.

391
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:27,220
What's wrong with Grandma Jin?

392
00:13:28,379 --> 00:13:29,179
Grandma Jin.

393
00:13:29,779 --> 00:13:30,980
Where does it hurt?

394
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,620
Where are the flower buds?

395
00:13:33,259 --> 00:13:35,460
Don't pick them. Wait for them to bloom.

396
00:13:36,379 --> 00:13:37,220
Royal Physician Sun.

397
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:38,659
Grandma Jin is getting on in years.

398
00:13:38,659 --> 00:13:39,860
For the details...

399
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:42,139
You'll have to ask Xiaofang.

400
00:13:43,259 --> 00:13:44,059
Xiaofang.

401
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:45,620
Grandma Jin's...

402
00:13:48,159 --> 00:13:48,559
You...

403
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:51,059
Why are you eating snacks during work hours?

404
00:13:51,379 --> 00:13:52,700
I wasn't eating snacks.

405
00:13:53,059 --> 00:13:53,740
This is President Li...

406
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:54,840
President Li just gave this to me.

407
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:55,779
She's just having a taste.

408
00:13:57,379 --> 00:13:59,299
You're accepting gifts from an elder?

409
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,659
No, Royal Physician Sun...

410
00:14:00,659 --> 00:14:01,340
Let me explain.

411
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:03,000
Save it. No need to explain.

412
00:14:03,379 --> 00:14:04,539
I know exactly what's going on.

413
00:14:04,779 --> 00:14:05,899
No, Sun...

414
00:14:07,139 --> 00:14:08,500
Xiaolan, what do you have to say?

415
00:14:25,299 --> 00:14:25,940
Stop right there

416
00:14:26,379 --> 00:14:27,379
Where are you going?

417
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:29,100
Taking Grandma Jin out for a walk.

418
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:30,460
Did you feed her?

419
00:14:30,460 --> 00:14:31,100
Yes, I did.

420
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,139
Did she take her medicine?

421
00:14:32,179 --> 00:14:32,980
Yes, she did.

422
00:14:33,220 --> 00:14:34,500
Then...

423
00:14:34,659 --> 00:14:36,460
Did you take her for a walk?

424
00:14:37,419 --> 00:14:38,299
Not yet.

425
00:14:38,299 --> 00:14:38,940
Look.

426
00:14:38,940 --> 00:14:40,220
How are you doing your job?

427
00:14:40,419 --> 00:14:42,700
Isn't that what I'm doing right now?

428
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,340
Well...

429
00:14:48,419 --> 00:14:49,580
Xiaolan.

430
00:14:49,899 --> 00:14:51,299
What are you looking for?

431
00:14:51,299 --> 00:14:52,159
I'm finding fault.

432
00:14:52,159 --> 00:14:52,860
No.

433
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:53,620
I'm looking for an excuse.

434
00:14:53,620 --> 00:14:54,460
No, not that either.

435
00:14:55,860 --> 00:14:56,659
I...

436
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:57,460
I'm checking to see...

437
00:14:57,460 --> 00:14:59,299
if there's any work you missed.

438
00:15:00,340 --> 00:15:01,139
Oh, right.

439
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:03,700
Did you give Gou'er Ye...

440
00:15:03,980 --> 00:15:05,220
a nail trim?

441
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:06,340
Did you cut his hair?

442
00:15:06,899 --> 00:15:07,600
No.

443
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,320
Why not?

444
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,379
Isn't that your job?

445
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:13,460
My job?

446
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:15,139
Why can't you do it?

447
00:15:15,179 --> 00:15:16,740
If I do it, does that mean you can't?

448
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:17,539
Go.

449
00:15:17,940 --> 00:15:19,419
But if I go...

450
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:20,940
who will walk Grandma Jin?

451
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:22,179
I'm here.

452
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:23,919
So...

453
00:15:25,059 --> 00:15:26,039
Grandma Jin.

454
00:15:26,039 --> 00:15:27,659
I'm going to leave for a bit.

455
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,500
I'll come back to keep you company later.

456
00:15:31,059 --> 00:15:33,220
Where did you buy that big watermelon?

457
00:15:33,899 --> 00:15:35,539
Grandma Jin.

458
00:15:35,679 --> 00:15:36,799
I'm busy.

459
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:37,740
You just...

460
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:39,100
stay here in the shade...

461
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:40,379
and cool off by yourself.

462
00:15:45,460 --> 00:15:46,259
Xiaolan.

463
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:47,940
Dr. Chang, I...

464
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:50,259
I was just taking Grandma Jin for a walk.

465
00:15:50,779 --> 00:15:52,419
Why are you taking care of Grandma Jin again?

466
00:15:52,779 --> 00:15:53,460
Where is Xiaofang?

467
00:15:54,580 --> 00:15:56,139
She went out to meet her boyfriend.

468
00:15:56,139 --> 00:15:57,659
So I'm just doing a bit more to cover for her.

469
00:15:57,659 --> 00:15:58,940
She found a boyfriend already?

470
00:15:59,299 --> 00:16:00,179
Even if she found a boyfriend...

471
00:16:00,179 --> 00:16:01,500
she shouldn't go out during work hours.

472
00:16:02,340 --> 00:16:03,299
That's outrageous.

473
00:16:03,820 --> 00:16:04,779
Fine, thanks for your hard work.

474
00:16:04,779 --> 00:16:07,059
Little Chang, she didn't find a boyfriend.

475
00:16:07,659 --> 00:16:09,139
She went to buy me a big watermelon.

476
00:16:09,779 --> 00:16:10,659
Whenever this happens...

477
00:16:10,659 --> 00:16:12,460
your hearing suddenly works.

478
00:16:13,019 --> 00:16:13,980
I have things to do.

479
00:16:14,179 --> 00:16:15,059
You just...

480
00:16:15,059 --> 00:16:17,019
stay here quietly for a while.

481
00:16:17,659 --> 00:16:18,419
Wait.

482
00:16:18,419 --> 00:16:19,460
Wait, I...

483
00:16:20,299 --> 00:16:21,419
I have an emergency.

484
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:23,279
You said this sentence is...

485
00:16:24,460 --> 00:16:25,419
Grandma Jin.

486
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:26,940
Why are you here alone?

487
00:16:26,940 --> 00:16:27,820
Where's the caregiver?

488
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:30,500
This is bad.

489
00:16:31,299 --> 00:16:32,100
Xiaocai.

490
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:34,259
I need to use the toilet.

491
00:16:35,019 --> 00:16:35,820
No problem.

492
00:16:35,820 --> 00:16:37,100
I'll take you there.

493
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:37,500
Go away.

494
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:38,620
Take me where?

495
00:16:38,980 --> 00:16:40,299
You, a grown man...

496
00:16:40,299 --> 00:16:41,179
why are you meddling?

497
00:16:41,179 --> 00:16:42,220
It's okay, no problem.

498
00:16:43,779 --> 00:16:44,740
We Chinese people...

499
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:46,779
men and women keep their distance, understand?

500
00:16:46,980 --> 00:16:47,980
What does that mean?

501
00:16:47,980 --> 00:16:48,779
It means...

502
00:16:48,779 --> 00:16:50,259
that men and women...

503
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:51,779
I'm not explaining it to you.

504
00:16:52,179 --> 00:16:54,179
If I wait any longer, I won't make it.

505
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:54,960
Make...

506
00:16:55,159 --> 00:16:55,899
it?

507
00:16:57,940 --> 00:16:58,740
Oh dear.

508
00:16:59,779 --> 00:17:00,820
What happened?

509
00:17:00,940 --> 00:17:02,139
Still didn't make it.

510
00:17:07,420 --> 00:17:08,480
Giving patients the wrong medicine

511
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:11,339
Snacking during work hours

512
00:17:11,740 --> 00:17:13,460
Meeting your boyfriend on the clock

513
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:14,779
Soliciting red envelopes

514
00:17:14,779 --> 00:17:16,019
Accepting gifts

515
00:17:16,220 --> 00:17:17,299
Neglecting the elderly

516
00:17:17,299 --> 00:17:18,259
Causing Grandma Jin...

517
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:19,299
Come here

518
00:17:20,059 --> 00:17:20,779
Give me an explanation

519
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:22,500
I won't explain

520
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:24,460
What kind of attitude is that?

521
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:25,940
I quit

522
00:17:25,940 --> 00:17:27,019
Is that good enough for you?

523
00:17:28,660 --> 00:17:30,019
You think you're in the right?

524
00:17:31,539 --> 00:17:32,380
I'm so furious

525
00:17:32,380 --> 00:17:33,299
I'm really furious

526
00:17:35,539 --> 00:17:36,900
That's how the real world is

527
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:38,380
Every workplace

528
00:17:38,579 --> 00:17:40,259
has these deceitful schemers

529
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:41,880
who thrive like fish in water

530
00:17:42,059 --> 00:17:42,819
No

531
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:44,099
I have to step in

532
00:17:53,539 --> 00:17:54,740
I've made up my mind.

533
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:56,059
I'm leaving tomorrow.

534
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:56,859
Don't go.

535
00:17:56,859 --> 00:17:57,660
Don't leave!

536
00:17:58,140 --> 00:17:59,619
With Xiaolan here,

537
00:17:59,859 --> 00:18:01,380
I can't do this job.

538
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:04,119
Xiaofang, don't be so impulsive.

539
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,759
You're the joy of Changqingju.

540
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:07,539
If you leave,

541
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,000
the elders will be so upset.

542
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:09,720
Exactly.

543
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:11,599
Brother Yusheng, stop talking.

544
00:18:11,819 --> 00:18:12,420
I...

545
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:15,079
I can't bear to leave the elders either.

546
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,799
Especially Grandma Jin.

547
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,519
She treats you like her own granddaughter.

548
00:18:18,519 --> 00:18:20,680
If you go, you're dumping her on Xiaolan?

549
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,279
That's right.

550
00:18:21,279 --> 00:18:22,319
Grandma Jin...

551
00:18:22,559 --> 00:18:23,400
Grandma Jin...

552
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:26,240
I feel like she's my own grandmother.

553
00:18:28,559 --> 00:18:30,519
But I've already said the words.

554
00:18:30,519 --> 00:18:31,640
What are you afraid of?

555
00:18:32,039 --> 00:18:33,519
I'll write you a certificate tomorrow.

556
00:18:33,519 --> 00:18:34,880
You get the elders to sign it.

557
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,000
It'll definitely work.

558
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,279
Childish.

559
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,279
That's kid stuff.

560
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,079
What signature?

561
00:18:42,759 --> 00:18:43,759
What certificate?

562
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:45,799
None of that works.

563
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,880
The urgent task right now

564
00:18:48,279 --> 00:18:50,559
is for Xiaofang to write a detailed,

565
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:52,079
concise,

566
00:18:52,079 --> 00:18:54,319
and material-rich resignation report.

567
00:18:55,319 --> 00:18:56,440
Why resign?

568
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:58,960
Lao Li, what kind of idea is that?

569
00:18:59,279 --> 00:19:00,000
Isn't this

570
00:19:00,259 --> 00:19:01,279
eating salt when you're thirsty,

571
00:19:01,279 --> 00:19:02,539
wearing cotton when you're hot?

572
00:19:03,319 --> 00:19:04,839
Yes, Grandpa President Li.

573
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,359
I'm still on probation.

574
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,960
I can just leave.

575
00:19:09,119 --> 00:19:11,279
Why write a resignation report?

576
00:19:11,279 --> 00:19:11,920
No.

577
00:19:12,519 --> 00:19:14,279
This resignation report must be written.

578
00:19:15,359 --> 00:19:16,680
Young people

579
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,319
